ic forenames:  French Antoine, Jacques, Yves, Andre, Armand, Emile, Fernand, Marcel, Marthe, Remi, Alcide, Camille.","English (of Norman origin) and French: habitational name from any of several places in France, for example in Manche and Somme, that are named with Old French <i>beu</i>, <i>bel</i> ‘fair, lovely’ + <i>champ(s)</i> ‘field, plain’ (from Latin <i>bello campo</i> ‘beautiful field’). In English the surname is generally pronounced   Beecham  . Compare   Bushaw  .","English: in some cases, an Anglo-Norman French adaptation of Scottish   Campbell  , by translation into French of the folk etymology <i>de campo bello</i> ‘from the fair field’."],"variants":[{"name":"Beecham","meanings":["English (Lincolnshire): variant of   Beauchamp  , reflecting the normal English pronunciation."]},{"name":"Beachem","meanings":["English (Somerset and Gloucestershire): variant of   Beauchamp  ."]},{"name":"Beachum","meanings":["Altered form of English   Beauchamp  ."]},{"name":"Bagent","meanings":["English:","possibly a colloquial pronunciation of   Beauchamp   or   Beecham  . Old French <i>Beau-</i> often appears as <i>Be(e)-</i> in English surnames. The <i>-ch-</i> has been voiced and excrescent <i>-t</i> has been added.","perhaps an Anglicized form of a French or Flemish surname such as <b>Beaujean</b> and <b>Bejean</b>, from Old French <i>bel Jehan</i> ‘handsome John’ + excrescent <i>-t</i>. It could have been introduced to England in the 15th or 16th century by Flemish migrants."]},{"name":"Beacham","meanings":["English (of Norman origin): variant of   Beauchamp  ."]},{"name":"Campbell","meanings":["Scottish: nickname from Gaelic <i>cam</i> ‘crooked, bent’ + <i>beul</i> ‘mouth’. As a result of folk etymology, the surname was often represented in Latin documents as <i>de bello campo</i> ‘of the fair field’, which led to the name sometimes being ‘translated’ into Anglo-Norman French as   Beauchamp  .","Irish (North Armagh): adopted for Gaelic <b>Mac Cathmhaoil</b> ‘son of Cathmhaol’ (literally ‘battle chief’): see   Caulfield   and   Cowell  .","English: variant of   Camel  , under the influence of the Scottish name (see 1 above)."]},{"name":"Bushaw","meanings":["Americanized form of French   Beauchamp   and   Bouchard  ."]},{"name":"Beacom","meanings":["English (Somerset) and Irish (Fermanagh): of Norman origin, a variant of   Beauchamp  ."]}]}],"lifeSummary":"de Beauchamp was born about 0915, in Scotland. She had at least 1 son with Hugh I de Beauchamp."},"et":{"about 0915–":"umbes 0915–Surnud","0915–1008":"0915–1008","0950–1008":"0950–1008","0915–Female":"0915–Surnud","1008":"1008","0950":"0950","950":"0950","0915":"0915","about 0915":"umbes 0915","Normandie, France":"Normandie, Prantsusmaa","Scotland":"Scotland"},"fi":{"about 0915–":"noin 0915–Kuollut","0915–1008":"0915–1008","0950–1008":"0950–1008","0915–Female":"0915–Kuollut","1008":"1008","0950":"0950","950":"0950","0915":"0915","about 0915":"noin 0915","Normandie, France":"Normandie, Ranska","Scotland":"Scotland"},"fr":{"about 0915–":"environ 0915–Décédée","0915–1008":"0915–1008","0950–1008":"0950–1008","0915–Female":"0915–Décédée","1008":"1008","0950":"0950","950":"0950","0915":"0915","about 0915":"environ 0915","Normandie, France":"Normandie, France","Scotland":"Écosse","lifeSummary":"de Beauchamp est née environ 0915, à Écosse. Elle a eu au moins 1 fils avec Hugh I de Beauchamp."},"de":{"about 0915–":"um 0915–Verstorben","0915–1008":"0915–1008","0950–1008":"0950–1008","0915–Female":"0915–Verstorben","1008":"1008","0950":"0950","950":"0950","0915":"0915","about 0915":"um 0915","Normandie, France":"Normandie, Frankreich","Scotland":"Scotland","lifeSummary":"de Beauchamp wurde um 0915 in Scotland geboren. Sie hatte mit Hugh I de Beauchamp mindestens 1 Sohn."},"ht":{"about 0915–":"about 0915–Desede","0915–1008":"0915–1008","0950–1008":"0950–1008","0915–Female":"0915–Desede","1008":"1008","0950":"0950","950":"0950","0915":"0915","about 0915":"about 0915","Normandie, France":"N